{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":371,"text":"Steve Ramirez: My first\nyear of grad school,"},{"time":2491,"text":"I found myself in my bedroom"},{"time":3931,"text":"eating lots of Ben &amp; Jerry's"},{"time":6231,"text":"watching some trashy TV"},{"time":7915,"text":"and maybe, maybe listening\nto Taylor Swift."},{"time":11142,"text":"I had just gone through a breakup."},{"time":12883,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":14330,"text":"So for the longest time, all I would do"},{"time":16526,"text":"is recall the memory of this\nperson over and over again,"},{"time":20342,"text":"wishing that I could get\nrid of that gut-wrenching,"},{"time":22835,"text":"visceral \"blah\" feeling."},{"time":25368,"text":"Now, as it turns out,\nI'm a neuroscientist,"},{"time":27651,"text":"so I knew that the memory of that person"},{"time":30053,"text":"and the awful, emotional undertones\nthat color in that memory,"},{"time":33193,"text":"are largely mediated\nby separate brain systems."},{"time":35827,"text":"And so I thought, what if we could\ngo into the brain"},{"time":38328,"text":"and edit out that nauseating feeling"},{"time":40282,"text":"but while keeping the memory\nof that person intact?"},{"time":43252,"text":"Then I realized, maybe\nthat's a little bit lofty for now."},{"time":45943,"text":"So what if we could start\noff by going into the brain"},{"time":48456,"text":"and just finding a single\nmemory to begin with?"},{"time":51089,"text":"Could we jump-start\nthat memory back to life,"},{"time":53603,"text":"maybe even play with the contents\nof that memory?"},{"time":57471,"text":"All that said, there is one person\nin the entire world right now"},{"time":59700,"text":"that I really hope is not\nwatching this talk."},{"time":61867,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":65696,"text":"So there is a catch. There is a catch."},{"time":68985,"text":"These ideas probably remind\nyou of \"Total Recall,\""},{"time":71773,"text":"\"Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind,\""},{"time":73747,"text":"or of \"Inception.\""},{"time":75050,"text":"But the movie stars that we work with"},{"time":76836,"text":"are the celebrities of the lab."},{"time":78569,"text":"Xu Liu: Test mice."},{"time":80469,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":81597,"text":"As neuroscientists, we work\nin the lab with mice"},{"time":84751,"text":"trying to understand how memory works."},{"time":88161,"text":"And today, we hope\nto convince you that now"},{"time":90730,"text":"we are actually able to activate\na memory in the brain"},{"time":93946,"text":"at the speed of light."},{"time":96116,"text":"To do this, there's only two simple\nsteps to follow."},{"time":99222,"text":"First, you find and label\na memory in the brain,"},{"time":102732,"text":"and then you activate it with a switch."},{"time":106362,"text":"As simple as that."},{"time":107807,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":109629,"text":"SR: Are you convinced?"},{"time":111474,"text":"So, turns out finding a memory\nin the brain isn't all that easy."},{"time":115195,"text":"XL: Indeed. This is way more\ndifficult than, let's say,"},{"time":117998,"text":"finding a needle in a haystack,"},{"time":120402,"text":"because at least, you know,\nthe needle is still something"},{"time":123141,"text":"you can physically put your fingers on."},{"time":125491,"text":"But memory is not."},{"time":127468,"text":"And also, there's way\nmore cells in your brain"},{"time":130506,"text":"than the number of straws\nin a typical haystack."},{"time":135572,"text":"So yeah, this task does\nseem to be daunting."},{"time":138451,"text":"But luckily, we got help\nfrom the brain itself."},{"time":142130,"text":"It turned out that all we need\nto do is basically"},{"time":144585,"text":"to let the brain form a memory,"},{"time":146578,"text":"and then the brain will tell\nus which cells are involved"},{"time":150408,"text":"in that particular memory."},{"time":152174,"text":"SR: So what was going on in my brain"},{"time":154531,"text":"while I was recalling the memory of an ex?"},{"time":156625,"text":"If you were to just completely\nignore human ethics for a second"},{"time":159027,"text":"and slice up my brain right now,"},{"time":160695,"text":"you would see that there\nwas an amazing number"},{"time":162910,"text":"of brain regions that were active\nwhile recalling that memory."},{"time":165891,"text":"Now one brain region\nthat would be robustly active"},{"time":168803,"text":"in particular is called the hippocampus,"},{"time":170810,"text":"which for decades has\nbeen implicated in processing"},{"time":173265,"text":"the kinds of memories\nthat we hold near and dear,"},{"time":175681,"text":"which also makes it\nan ideal target to go into"},{"time":178255,"text":"and to try and find and maybe\nreactivate a memory."},{"time":181040,"text":"XL: When you zoom in into the hippocampus,"},{"time":183434,"text":"of course you will see lots of cells,"},{"time":185782,"text":"but we are able to find\nwhich cells are involved"},{"time":188813,"text":"in a particular memory,"},{"time":190289,"text":"because whenever a cell is active,"},{"time":192907,"text":"like when it's forming a memory,"},{"time":194455,"text":"it will also leave a footprint\nthat will later allow us to know"},{"time":198128,"text":"these cells are recently active."},{"time":200830,"text":"SR: So the same way\nthat building lights at night"},{"time":203188,"text":"let you know that somebody's probably\nworking there at any given moment,"},{"time":206641,"text":"in a very real sense, there\nare biological sensors"},{"time":209226,"text":"within a cell that are turned on"},{"time":211180,"text":"only when that cell was just working."},{"time":213315,"text":"They're sort of biological\nwindows that light up"},{"time":215625,"text":"to let us know that that cell\nwas just active."},{"time":217840,"text":"XL: So we clipped part of this sensor,"},{"time":219998,"text":"and attached that to a switch\nto control the cells,"},{"time":223145,"text":"and we packed this switch\ninto an engineered virus"},{"time":227045,"text":"and injected that into the brain\nof the mice."},{"time":229633,"text":"So whenever a memory is being formed,"},{"time":232267,"text":"any active cells for that memory"},{"time":234615,"text":"will also have this switch installed."},{"time":237357,"text":"SR: So here is what the hippocampus\nlooks like"},{"time":239572,"text":"after forming a fear memory, for example."},{"time":241822,"text":"The sea of blue that you see here"},{"time":243962,"text":"are densely packed brain cells,"},{"time":245914,"text":"but the green brain cells,"},{"time":247459,"text":"the green brain cells\nare the ones that are holding on"},{"time":250055,"text":"to a specific fear memory."},{"time":251398,"text":"So you are looking at the crystallization"},{"time":253377,"text":"of the fleeting formation of fear."},{"time":255764,"text":"You're actually looking\nat the cross-section of a memory right now."},{"time":259261,"text":"XL: Now, for the switch\nwe have been talking about,"},{"time":261714,"text":"ideally, the switch has\nto act really fast."},{"time":264639,"text":"It shouldn't take minutes\nor hours to work."},{"time":267218,"text":"It should act at the speed\nof the brain, in milliseconds."},{"time":271482,"text":"SR: So what do you think, Xu?"},{"time":272912,"text":"Could we use, let's say,\npharmacological drugs"},{"time":275514,"text":"to activate or inactivate brain cells?"},{"time":277352,"text":"XL: Nah. Drugs are pretty messy.\nThey spread everywhere."},{"time":281415,"text":"And also it takes them\nforever to act on cells."},{"time":284423,"text":"So it will not allow us\nto control a memory in real time."},{"time":288072,"text":"So Steve, how about let's zap\nthe brain with electricity?"},{"time":292366,"text":"SR: So electricity is pretty fast,"},{"time":294671,"text":"but we probably wouldn't\nbe able to target it"},{"time":296410,"text":"to just the specific cells\nthat hold onto a memory,"},{"time":298863,"text":"and we'd probably fry the brain."},{"time":300642,"text":"XL: Oh. That's true.\nSo it looks like, hmm,"},{"time":303837,"text":"indeed we need to find a better way"},{"time":306448,"text":"to impact the brain at the speed of light."},{"time":309743,"text":"SR: So it just so happens that light\ntravels at the speed of light."},{"time":314829,"text":"So maybe we could activate\nor inactive memories"},{"time":318312,"text":"by just using light --"},{"time":319809,"text":"XL: That's pretty fast."},{"time":321164,"text":"SR: -- and because normally brain cells"},{"time":323049,"text":"don't respond to pulses of light,"},{"time":324645,"text":"so those that would respond\nto pulses of light"},{"time":326603,"text":"are those that contain\na light-sensitive switch."},{"time":329059,"text":"Now to do that, first we need\nto trick brain cells"},{"time":331005,"text":"to respond to laser beams."},{"time":332467,"text":"XL: Yep. You heard it right."},{"time":333537,"text":"We are trying to shoot\nlasers into the brain."},{"time":335704,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":337414,"text":"SR: And the technique that lets\nus do that is optogenetics."},{"time":340738,"text":"Optogenetics gave us this\nlight switch that we can use"},{"time":344020,"text":"to turn brain cells on or off,"},{"time":345528,"text":"and the name of that switch\nis channelrhodopsin,"},{"time":348045,"text":"seen here as these green dots\nattached to this brain cell."},{"time":350582,"text":"You can think of channelrhodopsin\nas a sort of light-sensitive switch"},{"time":353892,"text":"that can be artificially\ninstalled in brain cells"},{"time":356508,"text":"so that now we can use that switch"},{"time":358422,"text":"to activate or inactivate the brain\ncell simply by clicking it,"},{"time":361446,"text":"and in this case we click\nit on with pulses of light."},{"time":363994,"text":"XL: So we attach this light-sensitive\nswitch of channelrhodopsin"},{"time":367689,"text":"to the sensor we've been talking about"},{"time":369897,"text":"and inject this into the brain."},{"time":372352,"text":"So whenever a memory is being formed,"},{"time":375563,"text":"any active cell for that particular memory"},{"time":377790,"text":"will also have this light-sensitive\nswitch installed in it"},{"time":381274,"text":"so that we can control these cells"},{"time":383675,"text":"by the flipping of a laser\njust like this one you see."},{"time":387939,"text":"SR: So let's put all of this\nto the test now."},{"time":390803,"text":"What we can do is we can take our mice"},{"time":392938,"text":"and then we can put them in a box\nthat looks exactly like this box here,"},{"time":395866,"text":"and then we can give them\na very mild foot shock"},{"time":398206,"text":"so that they form a fear\nmemory of this box."},{"time":400278,"text":"They learn that something\nbad happened here."},{"time":402361,"text":"Now with our system,\nthe cells that are active"},{"time":404703,"text":"in the hippocampus\nin the making of this memory,"},{"time":407493,"text":"only those cells will now\ncontain channelrhodopsin."},{"time":410376,"text":"XL: When you are as small as a mouse,"},{"time":413393,"text":"it feels as if the whole\nworld is trying to get you."},{"time":416988,"text":"So your best response of defense"},{"time":418736,"text":"is trying to be undetected."},{"time":421218,"text":"Whenever a mouse is in fear,"},{"time":423251,"text":"it will show this very typical behavior"},{"time":425133,"text":"by staying at one corner of the box,"},{"time":426902,"text":"trying to not move any part of its body,"},{"time":429664,"text":"and this posture is called freezing."},{"time":432959,"text":"So if a mouse remembers that something\nbad happened in this box,"},{"time":437253,"text":"and when we put them\nback into the same box,"},{"time":439876,"text":"it will basically show freezing"},{"time":441680,"text":"because it doesn't want to be detected"},{"time":443965,"text":"by any potential threats in this box."},{"time":446660,"text":"SR: So you can think of freezing as,"},{"time":448015,"text":"you're walking down the street\nminding your own business,"},{"time":450230,"text":"and then out of nowhere\nyou almost run into"},{"time":452302,"text":"an ex-girlfriend or ex-boyfriend,"},{"time":454147,"text":"and now those terrifying two seconds"},{"time":456281,"text":"where you start thinking, \"What do I do?\nDo I say hi?"},{"time":458157,"text":"Do I shake their hand? Do\nI turn around and run away?"},{"time":459525,"text":"Do I sit here and pretend\nlike I don't exist?\""},{"time":461554,"text":"Those kinds of fleeting thoughts\nthat physically incapacitate you,"},{"time":464738,"text":"that temporarily give you\nthat deer-in-headlights look."},{"time":467484,"text":"XL: However, if you put the mouse\nin a completely different"},{"time":470775,"text":"new box, like the next one,"},{"time":473936,"text":"it will not be afraid of this box"},{"time":476083,"text":"because there's no reason that it\nwill be afraid of this new environment."},{"time":480812,"text":"But what if we put\nthe mouse in this new box"},{"time":483992,"text":"but at the same time,\nwe activate the fear memory"},{"time":487603,"text":"using lasers just like we did before?"},{"time":490282,"text":"Are we going to bring back the fear memory"},{"time":493136,"text":"for the first box into this\ncompletely new environment?"},{"time":497133,"text":"SR: All right,\nand here's the million-dollar experiment."},{"time":499868,"text":"Now to bring back to life\nthe memory of that day,"},{"time":502781,"text":"I remember that the Red Sox had just won,"},{"time":504964,"text":"it was a green spring day,"},{"time":506873,"text":"perfect for going up and down the river"},{"time":508755,"text":"and then maybe going to the North End"},{"time":511024,"text":"to get some cannolis, #justsaying."},{"time":513183,"text":"Now Xu and I, on the other hand,"},{"time":516285,"text":"were in a completely windowless black room"},{"time":519115,"text":"not making any ocular movement\nthat even remotely resembles an eye blink"},{"time":522775,"text":"because our eyes were fixed\nonto a computer screen."},{"time":525242,"text":"We were looking at this mouse\nhere trying to activate a memory"},{"time":528219,"text":"for the first time using our technique."},{"time":530102,"text":"XL: And this is what we saw."},{"time":532369,"text":"When we first put the mouse into this box,"},{"time":534571,"text":"it's exploring, sniffing\naround, walking around,"},{"time":537684,"text":"minding its own business,"},{"time":539373,"text":"because actually by nature,"},{"time":541074,"text":"mice are pretty curious animals."},{"time":543053,"text":"They want to know, what's going\non in this new box?"},{"time":545675,"text":"It's interesting."},{"time":547206,"text":"But the moment we turned\non the laser, like you see now,"},{"time":550657,"text":"all of a sudden the mouse\nentered this freezing mode."},{"time":553689,"text":"It stayed here and tried not\nto move any part of its body."},{"time":558120,"text":"Clearly it's freezing."},{"time":559748,"text":"So indeed, it looks\nlike we are able to bring back"},{"time":562331,"text":"the fear memory for the first box"},{"time":564395,"text":"in this completely new environment."},{"time":567762,"text":"While watching this, Steve and I"},{"time":569874,"text":"are as shocked as the mouse itself."},{"time":572007,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":573269,"text":"So after the experiment,\nthe two of us just left the room"},{"time":576576,"text":"without saying anything."},{"time":578329,"text":"After a kind of long,\nawkward period of time,"},{"time":581725,"text":"Steve broke the silence."},{"time":583937,"text":"SR: \"Did that just work?\""},{"time":586278,"text":"XL: \"Yes,\" I said. \"Indeed it worked!\""},{"time":589252,"text":"We're really excited about this."},{"time":591369,"text":"And then we published our findings"},{"time":593993,"text":"in the journal Nature."},{"time":595689,"text":"Ever since the publication of our work,"},{"time":598160,"text":"we've been receiving numerous comments"},{"time":600575,"text":"from all over the Internet."},{"time":602700,"text":"Maybe we can take a look at some of those."},{"time":606450,"text":"[\"OMGGGGG FINALLY... so much more to come, virtual reality, neural manipulation, visual dream emulation...\nneural coding, 'writing and re-writing of memories', mental illnesses. Ahhh the future is awesome\"]"},{"time":608907,"text":"SR: So the first thing\nthat you'll notice is that people"},{"time":610907,"text":"have really strong opinions\nabout this kind of work."},{"time":613810,"text":"Now I happen to completely\nagree with the optimism"},{"time":616364,"text":"of this first quote,"},{"time":617180,"text":"because on a scale\nof zero to Morgan Freeman's voice,"},{"time":619988,"text":"it happens to be\none of the most evocative accolades"},{"time":622489,"text":"that I've heard come our way."},{"time":624039,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":625857,"text":"But as you'll see, it's not\nthe only opinion that's out there."},{"time":627808,"text":"[\"This scares the hell out of me... What if they could do that easily\nin humans in a couple of years?! OH MY GOD WE'RE DOOMED\"]"},{"time":629372,"text":"XL: Indeed, if we take\na look at the second one,"},{"time":631682,"text":"I think we can all agree that it's, meh,"},{"time":633789,"text":"probably not as positive."},{"time":635772,"text":"But this also reminds us that,"},{"time":637957,"text":"although we are still working with mice,"},{"time":640143,"text":"it's probably a good idea\nto start thinking and discussing"},{"time":643660,"text":"about the possible ethical ramifications"},{"time":646651,"text":"of memory control."},{"time":648599,"text":"SR: Now, in the spirit of the third quote,"},{"time":650799,"text":"we want to tell you about a recent\nproject that we've been"},{"time":652773,"text":"working on in lab that we've called\nProject Inception."},{"time":655369,"text":"[\"They should make a movie about this. Where they plant ideas into peoples minds,\nso they can control them for their own personal gain. We'll call it: Inception.\"]"},{"time":658612,"text":"So we reasoned that now\nthat we can reactivate a memory,"},{"time":662178,"text":"what if we do so but then begin\nto tinker with that memory?"},{"time":665130,"text":"Could we possibly even turn\nit into a false memory?"},{"time":668163,"text":"XL: So all memory\nis sophisticated and dynamic,"},{"time":672262,"text":"but if just for simplicity,\nlet's imagine memory"},{"time":675241,"text":"as a movie clip."},{"time":676643,"text":"So far what we've told you\nis basically we can control"},{"time":679313,"text":"this \"play\" button of the clip"},{"time":681244,"text":"so that we can play this video\nclip any time, anywhere."},{"time":685829,"text":"But is there a possibility\nthat we can actually get"},{"time":688360,"text":"inside the brain and edit this movie clip"},{"time":691220,"text":"so that we can make it\ndifferent from the original?"},{"time":694116,"text":"Yes we can."},{"time":696294,"text":"Turned out that all we need\nto do is basically"},{"time":698509,"text":"reactivate a memory using\nlasers just like we did before,"},{"time":702699,"text":"but at the same time,\nif we present new information"},{"time":706138,"text":"and allow this new information\nto incorporate into this old memory,"},{"time":710112,"text":"this will change the memory."},{"time":712550,"text":"It's sort of like making a remix tape."},{"time":716213,"text":"SR: So how do we do this?"},{"time":719071,"text":"Rather than finding a fear\nmemory in the brain,"},{"time":721028,"text":"we can start by taking our animals,"},{"time":722744,"text":"and let's say we put them in a blue\nbox like this blue box here"},{"time":725721,"text":"and we find the brain cells\nthat represent that blue box"},{"time":728368,"text":"and we trick them to respond\nto pulses of light"},{"time":730631,"text":"exactly like we had said before."},{"time":732365,"text":"Now the next day, we can take\nour animals and place them"},{"time":734489,"text":"in a red box that they've never\nexperienced before."},{"time":737188,"text":"We can shoot light\ninto the brain to reactivate"},{"time":739451,"text":"the memory of the blue box."},{"time":741323,"text":"So what would happen here\nif, while the animal"},{"time":743067,"text":"is recalling the memory of the blue box,"},{"time":744996,"text":"we gave it a couple of mild foot shocks?"},{"time":747604,"text":"So here we're trying to artificially\nmake an association"},{"time":750297,"text":"between the memory of the blue box"},{"time":752212,"text":"and the foot shocks themselves."},{"time":753715,"text":"We're just trying to connect the two."},{"time":755501,"text":"So to test if we had done so,"},{"time":757037,"text":"we can take our animals once again"},{"time":758365,"text":"and place them back in the blue box."},{"time":760311,"text":"Again, we had just reactivated\nthe memory of the blue box"},{"time":763050,"text":"while the animal got a couple\nof mild foot shocks,"},{"time":765455,"text":"and now the animal suddenly freezes."},{"time":767586,"text":"It's as though it's recalling being\nmildly shocked in this environment"},{"time":770944,"text":"even though that never actually happened."},{"time":773790,"text":"So it formed a false memory,"},{"time":775652,"text":"because it's falsely\nfearing an environment"},{"time":777724,"text":"where, technically speaking,"},{"time":779082,"text":"nothing bad actually happened to it."},{"time":781266,"text":"XL: So, so far we are only talking about"},{"time":783719,"text":"this light-controlled \"on\" switch."},{"time":786085,"text":"In fact, we also have\na light-controlled \"off\" switch,"},{"time":789373,"text":"and it's very easy to imagine that"},{"time":791453,"text":"by installing this\nlight-controlled \"off\" switch,"},{"time":793931,"text":"we can also turn off a memory,\nany time, anywhere."},{"time":799519,"text":"So everything\nwe've been talking about today"},{"time":801733,"text":"is based on this philosophically\ncharged principle of neuroscience"},{"time":806410,"text":"that the mind, with its seemingly\nmysterious properties,"},{"time":810528,"text":"is actually made of physical\nstuff that we can tinker with."},{"time":814173,"text":"SR: And for me personally,"},{"time":815648,"text":"I see a world where we can reactivate"},{"time":817434,"text":"any kind of memory that we'd like."},{"time":819345,"text":"I also see a world where we can\nerase unwanted memories."},{"time":822643,"text":"Now, I even see a world\nwhere editing memories"},{"time":824810,"text":"is something of a reality,"},{"time":826118,"text":"because we're living in a time\nwhere it's possible"},{"time":827823,"text":"to pluck questions from the tree\nof science fiction"},{"time":830276,"text":"and to ground them\nin experimental reality."},{"time":832468,"text":"XL: Nowadays, people in the lab"},{"time":834351,"text":"and people in other\ngroups all over the world"},{"time":836737,"text":"are using similar methods\nto activate or edit memories,"},{"time":840554,"text":"whether that's old or new,\npositive or negative,"},{"time":844395,"text":"all sorts of memories so\nthat we can understand"},{"time":847067,"text":"how memory works."},{"time":848931,"text":"SR: For example, one group in our lab"},{"time":850715,"text":"was able to find the brain cells\nthat make up a fear memory"},{"time":853353,"text":"and converted them into a pleasurable\nmemory, just like that."},{"time":856128,"text":"That's exactly what I mean about editing\nthese kinds of processes."},{"time":859295,"text":"Now one dude in lab\nwas even able to reactivate"},{"time":861558,"text":"memories of female mice in male mice,"},{"time":863503,"text":"which rumor has it\nis a pleasurable experience."},{"time":866498,"text":"XL: Indeed, we are living\nin a very exciting moment"},{"time":870615,"text":"where science doesn't have\nany arbitrary speed limits"},{"time":874420,"text":"but is only bound by our own imagination."},{"time":877607,"text":"SR: And finally, what do\nwe make of all this?"},{"time":879774,"text":"How do we push this technology forward?"},{"time":881725,"text":"These are the questions\nthat should not remain"},{"time":883940,"text":"just inside the lab,"},{"time":885237,"text":"and so one goal of today's talk\nwas to bring everybody"},{"time":887833,"text":"up to speed with the kind\nof stuff that's possible"},{"time":890238,"text":"in modern neuroscience,"},{"time":891512,"text":"but now, just as importantly,"},{"time":893022,"text":"to actively engage everybody\nin this conversation."},{"time":896354,"text":"So let's think together as a team\nabout what this all means"},{"time":899140,"text":"and where we can and should go from here,"},{"time":901157,"text":"because Xu and I think we all have"},{"time":903255,"text":"some really big decisions ahead of us."},{"time":905791,"text":"Thank you. XL: Thank you."},{"time":906916,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}